attributes.description: The category to place events in that have invalid categories. A category is invalid when it is not a string. By default events without a category are not displayed until this value is specified.

attributes.name: category-hide-dynamic
attributes.description: Sets whether categories specified in an event should be hidden if it's not defined in `categories`.

attributes.description: Set whether the `category` view should show all defined `categories` even if there are no events for a category.

attributes.name: category-text
attributes.description: If categories is a list of objects, you can use this to determine what property to print out as the category text on the calendar. You can provide a function to do some logic or just define the prop name. It's similar to item-text on v-select

attributes.description: Set property of *event*'s category. Instead of a property a function can be given which takes an event and returns the category.

attributes.description: A background color for all events or a function which accepts an event object passed to the calendar to return a color.

attributes.name: event-end
attributes.description: Set property of *event*'s end timestamp.

attributes.description: The height of an event in pixels in the `month` view and at the top of the `day` views.

attributes.name: event-margin-bottom
attributes.description: Margin bottom for event

attributes.name: event-more
attributes.description: Whether the more 'button' is displayed on a calendar with too many events in a given day. It will say something like '5 more' and when clicked generates a `click:more` event.

attributes.name: event-more-text
attributes.description: The text to display in the more 'button' given the number of hidden events.

attributes.name: event-name
attributes.description: Set property of *event*'s displayed name, or a function which accepts an event object passed to the calendar as the first argument and a flag signalling whether the name is for a timed event (true) or an event over a day.

attributes.name: event-overlap-mode
attributes.description: One of `stack`, `column`, or a custom render function

attributes.name: event-overlap-threshold
attributes.description: A value in minutes that's used to determine whether two timed events should be placed in column beside each other or should be treated as slightly overlapping events.

attributes.name: event-ripple

attributes.name: event-start
attributes.description: Set property of *event*'s start timestamp.

attributes.name: event-text-color
attributes.description: A text color for all events or a function which accepts an event object passed to the calendar to return a color.

attributes.name: event-timed
attributes.description: If Dates or milliseconds are used as the start or end timestamp of an event, this prop can be a string to a property on the event that is truthy if the event is a timed event or a function which takes the event and returns a truthy value if the event is a timed event.

attributes.name: events
attributes.description: An array of event objects with a property for a start timestamp and optionally a name and end timestamp. If an end timestamp is not given, the value of start will be used. If no name is given, you must provide an implementation for the `event` slot.

attributes.description: The first time to display in the `day` view. If specified, this overwrites any `firstInterval` value specified. This can be the number of minutes since midnight, a string in the format of `HH:mm`, or an object with number properties hour and minute.

attributes.name: interval-count

attributes.name: interval-width

slots.name: category
slots.description: The content placed in a category header for the `category` type. The category variable is null for events with invalid (non-string) categories.

slots.name: day
slots.description: The content that is placed in a `week` or `month` view. The day & time object is passed through this slots scope.

slots.name: day-body
slots.description: The content that is placed in a `day` view in the scrollable interval container. The day & time object is passed through this slots scope.

vue-properties.name: timeToY
vue-properties.type: (time: string | number | {hour: number, minute: number}, clamp: boolean = false): number | false

vue-properties.name: timeDelta
vue-properties.type: (time: string | number | {hour: number, minute: number}): number | false

slots.name: day-header
slots.description: The content that is placed in a `day` view in the top container. The day & time object is passed through this slots scope.

vue-properties.name: timeToY
vue-properties.type: (time: string | number | {hour: number, minute: number}, clamp: boolean = false): number | false

vue-properties.name: timeDelta
vue-properties.type: (time: string | number | {hour: number, minute: number}): number | false

slots.name: day-label
slots.description: The content that is placed in the day of the month space in the `custom-weekly` or `month` view. The day & time object is passed through this slots scope.

slots.name: day-label-header
slots.description: The content that is placed in the day of the month space in the `week`, `day`, `4day`, or `custom-daily` view. The day & time object is passed through this slots scope.

slots.name: day-month
slots.description: The content that is placed in the month space in the `week` or `month` view. The day & time object is passed through this slots scope.

slots.name: event
slots.description: The content placed in an event. This ignores the `event-name` prop.

slots.name: interval
slots.description: The content that is placed in the interval space in the `day` view. The day & time object is passed through this slots scope.

attributes.name: color
attributes.description: Applies specified color to the control - it can be the name of material color (for example `success` or `purple`) or css color (`#033` or `rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5)`). You can find a list of built-in classes on the [colors page](/styles/colors#material-colors).

attributes.name: dark
attributes.description: Applies the dark theme variant to the component. You can find more information on the Material Design documentation for [dark themes](https://material.io/design/color/dark-theme.html).

attributes.name: day-format
attributes.description: Formats day of the month string that appears in a day to a specified locale

attributes.name: end
attributes.description: The ending date on the calendar (inclusive) in the format of `YYYY-MM-DD`. This may be ignored depending on the `type` of the calendar.

attributes.name: first-interval
attributes.description: The first interval to display in the `day` view. If `intervalMinutes` is set to 60 and this is set to 9 the first time in the view is 9am.

attributes.name: first-time
attributes.description: The first time to display in the `day` view. If specified, this overwrites any `firstInterval` value specified. This can be the number of minutes since midnight, a string in the format of `HH:mm`, or an object with number properties hour and minute.

attributes.name: hide-header
attributes.description: If the header at the top of the `day` view should be visible.

attributes.name: interval-count
attributes.description: The number of intervals to display in the `day` view.

attributes.name: interval-format
attributes.description: Formats time of day string that appears in the interval gutter of the `day` and `week` view to specified locale

attributes.name: interval-height
attributes.description: The height of an interval in pixels in the `day` view.

attributes.name: interval-minutes
attributes.description: The number of minutes the intervals are in the `day` view. A common interval is 60 minutes so the intervals are an hour.

attributes.name: interval-style
attributes.description: Returns CSS styling to apply to the interval.

attributes.name: interval-width
attributes.description: The width of the interval gutter on the left side in the `day` view.

attributes.name: light
attributes.description: Applies the light theme variant to the component.

attributes.name: locale
attributes.description: The locale of the calendar.

attributes.name: max-days
attributes.description: The maximum number of days to display in the custom calendar if an `end` day is not set.

attributes.name: now
attributes.description: Override the day & time which is considered now. This is in the format of `YYYY-MM-DD hh:mm:ss`. The calendar is styled according to now.

attributes.name: short-intervals
attributes.description: If true, the intervals in the `day` view will be 9 AM as opposed to 09:00 AM

attributes.name: short-weekdays
attributes.description: Whether the short versions of a weekday should be used (Mon vs Monday).

attributes.name: show-interval-label
attributes.description: Checks if a given day and time should be displayed in the interval gutter of the `day` view.

attributes.name: start
attributes.description: The starting date on the calendar (inclusive) in the format of `YYYY-MM-DD`. This may be ignored depending on the `type` of the calendar.

attributes.name: weekday-format
attributes.description: Formats day of the week string that appears in the header to specified locale

attributes.name: weekdays
attributes.description: Specifies which days of the week to display. To display Monday through Friday only, a value of `[1, 2, 3, 4, 5]` can be used. To display a week starting on Monday a value of `[1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 0]` can be used.

attributes.description: Reduces the height of the toolbar content to 48px (96px when using the **prominent** prop).

attributes.name: elevation
attributes.description: Designates an elevation applied to the component between 0 and 24. You can find more information on the [elevation page](/styles/elevation).

attributes.name: extended
attributes.description: Use this prop to increase the height of the toolbar _without_ using the `extension` slot for adding content. May be used in conjunction with the **extension-height** prop, and any of the other props that affect the height of the toolbar, e.g. **prominent**, **dense**, etc., **WITH THE EXCEPTION** of **height**.

attributes.name: extension-height
attributes.description: Specify an explicit height for the `extension` slot.

attributes.name: flat
attributes.description: Removes the toolbar's box-shadow.

attributes.name: floating
attributes.description: Applies **display: inline-flex** to the component.

attributes.name: height
attributes.description: Designates a specific height for the toolbar. Overrides the heights imposed by other props, e.g. **prominent**, **dense**, **extended**, etc.

attributes.name: light
attributes.description: Applies the light theme variant to the component.

attributes.name: max-height
attributes.description: Sets the maximum height for the component.

attributes.name: max-width
attributes.description: Sets the maximum width for the component.

attributes.name: min-height
attributes.description: Sets the minimum height for the component.

attributes.name: min-width
attributes.description: Sets the minimum width for the component.

attributes.name: outlined
attributes.description: Removes elevation (box-shadow) and adds a *thin* border.

attributes.name: prominent
attributes.description: Increases the height of the toolbar content to 128px.

attributes.name: rounded
attributes.description: Designates the **border-radius** applied to the component. You can find more information on the [Border Radius page](/styles/border-radius).

attributes.name: shaped
attributes.description: Applies a large border radius on the top left and bottom right of the card.

attributes.name: short
attributes.description: Reduce the height of the toolbar content to 56px (112px when using the **prominent** prop).

attributes.name: src
attributes.description: Specifies a [v-img](/components/images) as the component's background.

attributes.name: tag
attributes.description: Specify a custom tag used on the root element.

attributes.name: tile
attributes.description: Removes the component's **border-radius**.

attributes.name: width
attributes.description: Sets the width for the component.

slots.name: default
slots.description: The default Vue slot.

slots.name: extension
slots.description: Slot positioned directly under the main content of the toolbar. Height of this slot can be set explicitly with the **extension-height** prop. If this slot has no content, the **extended** prop may be used instead.

slots.name: img
slots.description: Expects the [v-img](/components/images) component. Scoped **props** should be applied with `v-bind="props"`.

attributes.name: tag
attributes.description: Specify a custom tag used on the root element.

slots.name: default
slots.description: The default Vue slot.

attributes.name: tag
attributes.description: Specify a custom tag used on the root element.

slots.name: default
slots.description: The default Vue slot.

attributes.name: absolute
attributes.description: Applies **position: absolute** to the component.

attributes.name: activator
attributes.description: Designate a custom activator when the `activator` slot is not used. String can be any valid querySelector and Object can be any valid Node.

attributes.name: allow-overflow
attributes.description: Removes overflow re-positioning for the content

attributes.name: attach
attributes.description: Specifies which DOM element that this component should detach to. String can be any valid querySelector and Object can be any valid Node. This will attach to the root `v-app` component by default.

attributes.name: bottom
attributes.description: Aligns the component towards the bottom.

attributes.name: close-delay
attributes.description: Delay (in ms) after which menu closes (when open-on-hover prop is set to true)

attributes.name: color
attributes.description: Applies specified color to the control - it can be the name of material color (for example `success` or `purple`) or css color (`#033` or `rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5)`). You can find a list of built-in classes on the [colors page](/styles/colors#material-colors).

attributes.name: content-class
attributes.description: Applies a custom class to the detached element. This is useful because the content is moved to the beginning of the `v-app` component (unless the **attach** prop is provided) and is not targetable by classes passed directly on the component.

attributes.name: disabled
attributes.description: Disables the tooltip

attributes.name: eager
attributes.description: Will force the components content to render on mounted. This is useful if you have content that will not be rendered in the DOM that you want crawled for SEO.

attributes.name: internal-activator
attributes.description: Designates whether to use an internal activator

attributes.name: left
attributes.description: Aligns the component towards the left.

attributes.name: max-width
attributes.description: Sets the maximum width for the content

attributes.name: min-width
attributes.description: Sets the minimum width for the content

attributes.name: nudge-bottom
attributes.description: Nudge the content to the bottom

attributes.name: nudge-left
attributes.description: Nudge the content to the left

attributes.name: nudge-right
attributes.description: Nudge the content to the right

attributes.name: nudge-top
attributes.description: Nudge the content to the top

attributes.name: nudge-width
attributes.description: Nudge the content width

attributes.name: offset-overflow
attributes.description: Causes the component to flip to the opposite side when repositioned due to overflow

attributes.name: open-delay
attributes.description: Delay (in ms) after which tooltip opens (when `open-on-hover` prop is set to **true**)

attributes.name: open-on-click
attributes.description: Designates whether the tooltip should open on activator click

attributes.name: open-on-hover
attributes.description: Designates whether the tooltip should open on activator hover

attributes.name: position-x
attributes.description: Used to position the content when not using an activator slot

attributes.name: position-y
attributes.description: Used to position the content when not using an activator slot

attributes.name: right
attributes.description: Aligns the component towards the right.

attributes.name: tag
attributes.description: Specifies a custom tag for the activator wrapper

attributes.name: top
attributes.description: Aligns the content towards the top.

attributes.name: transition
attributes.description: Sets the component transition. Can be one of the [built in transitions](/styles/transitions) or one your own.

attributes.name: value
attributes.description: Controls whether the component is visible or hidden.

attributes.name: z-index
attributes.description: The z-index used for the component

slots.name: activator
slots.description: When used, will activate the component when clicked (or hover for specific components). This manually stops the event propagation. Without this slot, if you open the component through its model, you will need to manually stop the event propagation

slots.name: default
slots.description: The default Vue slot.

attributes.name: activatable
attributes.description: Allows user to mark a node as active by clicking on it

attributes.name: active
attributes.description: Syncable prop that allows one to control which nodes are active. The array consists of the `item-key` of each active item.

attributes.name: active-class
attributes.description: The class applied to the node when active

attributes.name: color
attributes.description: Sets the color of the active node

attributes.name: dark
attributes.description: Applies the dark theme variant to the component. You can find more information on the Material Design documentation for [dark themes](https://material.io/design/color/dark-theme.html).

attributes.name: dense
attributes.description: Decreases the height of the items

attributes.name: disable-per-node
attributes.description: Prevents disabling children nodes

attributes.name: disabled
attributes.description: Disables selection for all nodes

attributes.name: expand-icon
attributes.description: Icon used to indicate that a node can be expanded

attributes.name: filter
attributes.description: Custom item filtering function. By default it will use case-insensitive search in item's label.

attributes.name: hoverable
attributes.description: Applies a hover class when mousing over nodes

attributes.name: indeterminate-icon
attributes.description: Icon used when node is in an indeterminate state. Only visible when `selectable` is `true`.

attributes.name: item-children
attributes.description: Property on supplied `items` that contains its children

attributes.name: item-disabled
attributes.description: Property on supplied `items` that contains the disabled state of the item

attributes.name: item-key
attributes.description: Property on supplied `items` used to keep track of node state. The value of this property has to be unique among all items.

attributes.name: item-text
attributes.description: Property on supplied `items` that contains its label text

attributes.name: items
attributes.description: An array of items used to build the treeview

attributes.name: light
attributes.description: Applies the light theme variant to the component.

attributes.name: load-children
attributes.description: A function used when dynamically loading children. If this prop is set, then the supplied function will be run if expanding an item that has a `item-children` property that is an empty array. Supports returning a Promise.

attributes.name: loading-icon
attributes.description: Icon used when node is in a loading state

attributes.name: multiple-active
attributes.description: When `true`, allows user to have multiple active nodes at the same time

attributes.name: off-icon
attributes.description: Icon used when node is not selected. Only visible when `selectable` is `true`.

attributes.name: on-icon
attributes.description: Icon used when leaf node is selected or when a branch node is fully selected. Only visible when `selectable` is `true`.

attributes.name: open
attributes.description: Syncable prop that allows one to control which nodes are open. The array consists of the `item-key` of each open item.

attributes.name: open-all
attributes.description: When `true` will cause all branch nodes to be opened when component is mounted

attributes.name: open-on-click
attributes.description: When `true` will cause nodes to be opened by clicking anywhere on it, instead of only opening by clicking on expand icon. When using this prop with `activatable` you will be unable to mark nodes with children as active.

attributes.name: return-object
attributes.description: When `true` will make `v-model`, `active.sync` and `open.sync` return the complete object instead of just the key

attributes.name: rounded
attributes.description: Provides an alternative active style for `v-treeview` node. Only visible when `activatable` is `true` and should not be used in conjunction with the `shaped` prop.

attributes.name: search
attributes.description: The search model for filtering results

attributes.name: selectable
attributes.description: Will render a checkbox next to each node allowing them to be selected

attributes.name: selected-color
attributes.description: The color of the selection checkbox

attributes.name: selection-type
attributes.description: Controls how the treeview selects nodes. There are two modes available: 'leaf' and 'independent'

attributes.name: shaped
attributes.description: Provides an alternative active style for `v-treeview` node. Only visible when `activatable` is `true` and should not be used in conjunction with the `rounded` prop.

attributes.name: transition
attributes.description: Applies a transition when nodes are opened and closed

attributes.name: value
attributes.description: Allows one to control which nodes are selected. The array consists of the `item-key` of each selected item. Is used with `@input` event to allow for `v-model` binding.

events.name: input
events.description: Emits the array of selected items when this value changes

events.name: update:active
events.description: Emits the array of active items when this value changes

events.name: update:open
events.description: Emits the array of open items when this value changes

slots.name: append
slots.description: Appends content after label

slots.name: label
slots.description: Label content

slots.name: prepend
slots.description: Prepends content before label

attributes.name: bench
attributes.description: The number of items **outside** the user view that are rendered (even if they are **not** viewable); to help prevent empty white space when scrolling *fast*.

attributes.name: height
attributes.description: Height of the component as a css value

attributes.name: item-height
attributes.description: Height in pixels of the items to display

attributes.name: items
attributes.description: The array of items to display

attributes.name: max-height
attributes.description: Sets the maximum height for the component.

attributes.name: max-width
attributes.description: Sets the maximum width for the component.

attributes.name: min-height
attributes.description: Sets the minimum height for the component.

attributes.name: min-width
attributes.description: Sets the minimum width for the component.

attributes.name: width
attributes.description: Sets the width for the component.

slots.name: default
slots.description: Default slot to customize items appearance

attributes.name: active-class
attributes.description: The **active-class** applied to children when they are activated.

attributes.name: continuous
attributes.description: If `true`, window will "wrap around" from the last item to the first, and from the first item to the last

attributes.name: dark
attributes.description: Applies the dark theme variant to the component. You can find more information on the Material Design documentation for [dark themes](https://material.io/design/color/dark-theme.html).

attributes.name: light
attributes.description: Applies the light theme variant to the component.

attributes.name: next-icon
attributes.description: Icon used for the "next" button if `show-arrows` is `true`

attributes.name: prev-icon
attributes.description: Icon used for the "prev" button if `show-arrows` is `true`

attributes.name: reverse
attributes.description: Reverse the normal transition direction.

attributes.name: show-arrows
attributes.description: Display the "next" and "prev" buttons

attributes.name: show-arrows-on-hover
attributes.description: Display the "next" and "prev" buttons on hover. `show-arrows` MUST ALSO be set.

attributes.name: tag
attributes.description: Specify a custom tag used on the root element.

attributes.name: touch
attributes.description: Provide a custom **left** and **right** function when swiped left or right.

attributes.name: touchless
attributes.description: Disable touch support.

attributes.name: value
attributes.description: The designated model value for the component.

attributes.name: value-comparator
attributes.description: Apply a custom value comparator function

attributes.name: vertical
attributes.description: Uses a vertical transition when changing windows.

events.name: change
events.description: Emitted when the component value is changed by user interaction

slots.name: default
slots.description: The default Vue slot.

slots.name: next
slots.description: Slot displaying the arrow switching to the next item

slots.name: prev
slots.description: Slot displaying the arrow switching to the previous item

attributes.name: active-class
attributes.description: Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active. You can find more information about the [**active-class** prop](https://router.vuejs.org/api/#active-class) on the vue-router documentation.

attributes.name: disabled
attributes.description: Prevents the item from becoming active when using the "next" and "prev" buttons or the `toggle` method

attributes.name: eager
attributes.description: Will force the components content to render on mounted. This is useful if you have content that will not be rendered in the DOM that you want crawled for SEO.

attributes.name: reverse-transition
attributes.description: Sets the reverse transition

attributes.name: transition
attributes.description: The transition used when the component progressing through items. Can be one of the [built in transitions](/styles/transitions) or one your own.

attributes.name: value
attributes.description: The value used when the component is selected in a group. If not provided, the index will be used.

slots.name: default
slots.description: The default Vue slot.

attributes.name: mode

attributes.name: origin
